<TITLE> BNP calls again for original JS seat order </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 9 (bdnews24.com)BNP and its allies will not join parliament unless the original seating order of the opposition is restored, the opposition chief whip Jainul Abedin Faruq on Monday. "We will consider going to parliament if the speakers specifically announces restoration of our seats to the previous order," he said at a press briefing on Monday at the chamber of the deputy leader of the opposition. Faruq also demanded guarantee that the names proposed by the opposition leader for parliamentary committees would not be changed. He said in one committee, the names of Salauddin Quader Chowdhury and M.K. Anwar were proposed, but the name of the Chowdhury was dropped. The BNP parliamentary party earlier held a meeting chaired by senior parliamentarian SQ Chowdhury. The meeting discussed two letters received from ruling chief whip Abdus Shahid and a meeting of a BNP delegation with speaker Abdul Hamid on Sunday. Faruq told the briefing: "We have informed the speaker that we want to go back to parliament. But he has not said anything specific on seat readjustments. The meeting decided if the speaker announces restoration of according to the previous order, we will consider going back to parliament". He added: "Chief whip Abdus Shahid gave us a letter seeking names for 48 of our MPs to sit on parliamentary committees." "We will consider sending names when we come to know which four parliamentary are to be chaired by opposition members". bdnews24
